item.description:

[quote=“Lin, post:17, topic:360769”][quote author=Davidi2 link=topic=457065.msg3347905#msg3347905 date=1284961835]

[quote author=Lin link=topic=457065.msg3347786#msg3347786 date=1284951906]
Very… boring. First off, try recording it with RuneScape in High Detail. Second, don’t use colored text if you’re going to use dark colors. Also try using the wave/2/3 effects. Don’t just sit in Lumbridge and other places using emotes. Go someplace exciting, like level 50 wilderness or something
[/quote]She told me she tried HD, but RSHD + Camtasia = uber lagg.

I’d also like to point out to everyone that this is before ANY video editing, and it’s the first draft, so don’t get too critical yet
[/quote]Camtasia is fucking terrible. It’s a resource hog and should be used when every other piece of video recording software is broken. Camstudio and HyperCam are way better choices.
[/quote]I have camstudio, idk what else she has.
[/quote]“She told me she tried HD, but RSHD + Camtasia = uber lagg. :(” ?[/quote]I’m not the one recording…

item.title: RuneScape Music Video
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

Not my type of music, but I would suggest not using chat effects (red, blue, etc) to speak. Also make sure you use video effects but do not over-do it. Don’t forget you can also use the Orb of Oculus for camera views, however I have not tried using it before.

Here is a good example of an RSMV that I like, and I was even in it. I am the guy in the beginning with the Bandos godsword and untrimmed cooking cape. Was so long ago.

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ka2TPfnHqyY

Read full topic
